[5] Ukraine (Odessa)
Date: Mon 11 Dec 2018, 6:34 PM
Source: 112 UA [edited]
https://112.international/society/three-year-old-boy-died-from-measles-in-odesa-region-35046.html


A 3-year-old boy died from measles at Odesa City Infectious Diseases Hospital, as Dumskaya reported.

He became the 3rd child in Odesa, who died from this disease in 2018. In total, 4 residents of Odesa died from measles.

Preliminarily, a child got infected in the regional children's clinical hospital, where he was treated after being diagnosed with bronchitis. When his state deteriorated, the doctors diagnosed pneumonia and sent the child to the infectious diseases hospital (there is a note in a medical history that the boy contacted with people infected with measles). Later, the boy was discharged but his state deteriorated in 5 days. The child was hospitalized in the infectious diseases hospital again. He also contacted with the possible carrier of measles.

According to his mother, the doctor explained the contact with an ill child by accident.

"He recommended giving him injections of immunoglobulin to prevent the infection. When he was discharged, he ran, moved. On [1 Dec 2018], he had fever and workers of the hospital said it looked like [he was] falling ill with measles. I gave him the prescribed medicines in the morning. He immediately felt bad. I told doctors but they said that it was ok, just consequences of measles," she said. Despite the fact that the child began to eat the night before, he died at night.

[...] Earlier, 45 school students and a pregnant teacher got sick with measles in Rukshyna village, Chernivtsi region, southwestern Ukraine. Later, it turned out that the majority of the affected were not vaccinated.

Besides, 28 children got sick with measles in one of the Vinnytsia region's schools. The measles outbreak is related to the fact that parents refuse to vaccinate their children.

The number of cases of measles in January-September 2018 has increased 17 times in comparison with the same period of time in 2017

