[7] Russia
Date: Sun 10 Dec 2018
Source: The Chennai Telegram [edited]
https://chtelegram.com/five-employees-of-the-samara-hypermarket-contracted-measles/14466


A total of 5 people working in the Samara hypermarket "Lenta" contracted measles in November--December this year [2018].

This was reported by the head of the regional Department of Rospotrebnadzor, Svetlana Arkhipova, said TASS. According to her, they are all employees of the hypermarket located in the shopping center "Aurora".

According to preliminary information, the 1st patients used to travel to Dagestan for personal reasons. In connection with the incident, the Mall carried out a complex of anti-epidemic measures. In addition, more than 350 employees of the "Aurora" were vaccinated.

In turn, the head of the Department of organization of medical aid of Ministry of health of the Samara region Ilya Sirota stressed that we are talking about a group scenario, rather than the measles outbreak. Doctors have written out from hospital 2 cases, he said.

Measles is an infectious viral disease that is transmitted by airborne droplets. Regional CPS said that for the first 10 months of this year [2018] in the Samara region there were 13 cases. In 2017--2016 years there was not a single case.

[Byline: Chemmal Saheb]

