[8] Philippines (Barangay Handumanan, Bacolod City)
Date: Sun 10 Dec 2018
Source: Sunstar Bacolod [edited]
https://www.sunstar.com.ph/article/1778049


A total of 4 inmates of the Bureau of Jail Management and Penology (BJMP) in Barangay Handumanan, Bacolod City were tested positive of measles.

Dr. Grace Tan, head of the City Health Office (CHO)-Environment Sanitation Division, said on [12 Nov 2018] that about 25 inmates have been suffering from fever and rashes inside BJMP-Handumanan. Of the 25 inmates, 19 inmates have been placed in the isolation area.

Tan added that 4 of the 5 inmates who underwent the swab test tested positive of measles.

On [14 Nov 2018], about 1000 inmates including the BJMP-Handumanan personnel were immunized by the CHO to stop the spread of the virus. [...]

[Byline: Merlinda A. Pedrosa]

